The Ambassador of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to Nigeria, His Excellency Adnan Mahmoud Bostaji, and the Senior Special Assistant to the president on Foreign Affairs and the Diaspora, held a meeting at the embassy of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia on Thursday. The visit included discussions on vital issues including that of Nigerian nationals residing in KSA, with “mutual interests and understanding reached on coordinating such issues.” According to the official twitter handle of the Saudi Arabian embassy, @KSAembassyNG, “Issues of common interest were discussed and understanding was reached on coordinating such issues,” the tweet read. Mrs. Dabiri-Erewa described the meeting as “very productive,” on her own twitter handle, @abikedabiri. “Very productive meeting and look forward to working further with you as we deal with issues relating to Nigerians in the KSA,” she tweeted. Execution of Nigerian in Saudi: Pathetic, tragic – Dabiri-Erewa Presidency appeals to Saudi for leniency over 20 Nigerians on death row 2014 Hajj:  Visa issuance to start tomorrow Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin